        "text": "## Pb²⁺–Chloride Stability Constant with Multiple Literature Citations\n\n**Measurement selected:** `vlm_177645` — the recommended (extrapolated to zero ionic strength) value for the first stepwise formation of PbCl⁺.\n\n| Property | Value |\n|---|---|\n| **Equilibrium** | Pb²⁺ + Cl⁻ ⇌ PbCl⁺ |\n| **Beta definition** | β₁ (beta_def_812) |\n| **log K** | **1.55** |\n| **Temperature** | 25 °C |\n| **Ionic strength** | 0 M (infinite dilution) |\n\nThis single measurement is backed by **67 linked literature citations** in NIST SRD-46 — far exceeding the ≥2 requirement. Here is a representative selection spanning the full date range:\n\n| # | Shortcut | Authors | Year | Journal / Source |\n|---|----------|---------|------|------------------|\n| 1 | 30RD | E. C. Righellato, C. W. Davies | 1930 | *Trans. Faraday Soc.*, **26**, 592 |\n| 2 | 31F | H. Fromherz | 1931 | *Z. Phys. Chem.*, **A153**, 376 |\n| 3 | 42GN | A. B. Garrett, M. V. Noble, S. Miller | 1942 | *J. Chem. Educ.*, **19**, 485 |\n| 4 | 49Jb | J. C. James | 1949 | *J. Amer. Chem. Soc.*, **71**, 3243 |\n| 5 | 55Na | G. H. Nancollas | 1955 | *J. Chem. Soc.*, 1458 |\n| 6 | 61NR | C. J. Nyman, D. K. Roe, R. A. Plane | 1961 | *J. Amer. Chem. Soc.*, **83**, 323 |\n| 7 | 71BHa | A. M. Bond, G. Hefter | 1971 | *J. Electroanal. Chem.*, **31**, 477 |\n| 8 | 73BH | A. M. Bond, G. Hefter | 1973 | *J. Electroanal. Chem.*, **42**, 1 |\n| 9 | 81BYM | R. H. Byrne, R. W. Young, W. L. Miller | 1981 | *J. Soln. Chem.*, **10**, 243 |\n| 10 | 84MB | F. J. Millero, R. H. Byrne | 1984 | *Geochim. Cosmochim. Acta*, **48**, 1145 |\n| 11 | 88FSd | D. Ferri, F. Salvatore | 1988 | *Ann. Chim. (Rome)*, **78**, 509 |\n| 12 | 90H | G. T. Hefter | 1990 | *Polyhedron*, **9**, 2429 |\n| 13 | 94CIO | X. Chen, R. M. Izatt, J. L. Oscarson | 1994 | *Chem. Rev.*, **94**, 467 |\n\n*(13 of 67 citations shown — the full set spans 1930–1994.)*",
