        "paragraph_index": 2,
        "text": "### Chemistry Insight\n\nThe log β₁ = 1.55 for PbCl⁺ at I = 0 is a well-established \"benchmark\" value in aqueous coordination chemistry. The enormous number of independent studies (67 references over six decades) reflects the importance of Pb²⁺–Cl⁻ speciation in environmental geochemistry, electroanalytical chemistry, and lead corrosion science. The moderate magnitude of the constant indicates a relatively weak, predominantly electrostatic interaction — consistent with Pb²⁺ being a borderline soft acid and Cl⁻ a borderline hard base.\n\n*Source: NIST Standard Reference Database 46 (Critically Selected Stability Constants of Metal Complexes).*",
